column5: Always nice to have company for breakfast...taken from the patio door 10 minutes ago.
Thats some nice company and land you got there

Breakfast at 07:48 AM ??? That used to be your lunch time !!!...All the fresh air must be making you hungry and tired like it does me...not sure if that is a good thing or not...  Nice to see the deer...we had a herd of about 15 out back a few days ago...most headed down towards the lake but 4 came across the front of our property...someone up the road must be feeding them...
They're pretty to look at now... but wait till they start treading in your wife's flower patch!!
Very cool Lew Ya should put some oats or something out for them.. we feed the rabbits so we can watch them in the morning!!
.. . and have them for lunch?

Nothings changed Norm, I've been up since 2:30 A.M., it's the deer that are the sleepyheads around these parts  And TJ, the neighbor puts out a couple pails of grain twice a day and it's like ringing the dinner bell for these guys.
Ya...  ummm... when your up before the deer... umm.....  i think its time for an intervention...
I am thinking Misfish(Brian) is gonna wanna visit you  around nov and say hi to your deer  friends
I see the deer...but I'm still looking for the rabbit.
2:30am?? You must've done a lot of nightshift work in your career. That's about the time I get to bed lol
37 years worth and I sure don't miss it

haha great stuff. Just noticed you were a firefighter. Glad to see you are enjoying your well deserved retirement after a career in servicing and protecting the public.. Looks like a great place you got there!
If Lew is like me mudder,theres no way, I will be allowed to shoot the FAMILY pets.LOL  Sure nice to look at eh Lew.  Thanks for sharing.
Fantastic Lew...I had a skunk in my backyard once but I would say this is better.
Looks pretty close to paradise to me.  Enjoy !

awesome stuff Lew.... I thought you said you weren't going to be able to post often as you'd be enjoying your new home and property...and I think you've treated us with 2 reports nad pictures since! haha  Keep' em comin.  cheers, RYan
What a beautiful sight first thing in the morning.  I get bunny rabbits, but that's about it around here  Joey
And Just think most who retire want to head south for the Texas and Florida snow you guys have a great place Lew very glad you can enjoy it for sure.
It is indeed a great way to start the morning Lew... but to be a stickler.. you neighbour isn't doing the deer any favours feeding them.
Geeezzzz...fresh jerky right outside the door and a nice garage to hang it in....
Afraid I don't have any say over what the neighbors do Wayne
Yah.. I know! He's not gonna listen to the new "kid" on the block either !
